{"type":"message","id":"a20a29d6","parentId":"a2e1096f","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:29:16.984Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-02-17 20:29 GMT+2] OPERATION: HTTP/2 QUADRIGA & SECURITY REPORT.\n\n1.  **Security Answers (Draft):**\n    *   *Sanitizer:* Used `orjson` (strict parsing) and `t-strings` logic (PEP 750 concept) to treat all inputs as untrusted. No `eval()` allowed.\n    *   *Grounding:* `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` is the \"Ground Truth\". OODA Loop forces console verification. No action without \"Observe\".\n\n2.  **Refactor (`src/core/network.py`):**\n    *   *Class:* `HFTClient(httpx.AsyncClient)`.\n    *   *Config:* `http2=True`, `limits=httpx.Limits(max_keepalive_connections=20)`.\n    *   *Logic:* Connection Reuse is native to `httpx`.\n    *   *Offset:* Implement `await asyncio.sleep(worker_id * 0.15)` at start.\n\n3.  **Optimization (E-Tag / Headers):**\n    *   *Research:* Check if DMarket returns `ETag` or `Last-Modified`.\n    *   *Action:* If yes, send `If-None-Match` headers. If no, rely on `orjson` speed.\n\n4.  **Quadriga Launch (Dry Run x4):**\n    *   Start 4 workers.\n    *   *Monitor:* `logs/*.log` for `429`.\n    *   *Archivist:* Analyze rate limit headers (`X-RateLimit-Remaining`).\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Security Summary.\n    *   Quadriga Table (Ping/Interval).\n    *   Archivist Verdict (429 status).\n    *   Ready for Real Money."}],"timestamp":1771352956982}}
{"type":"message","id":"06cf86e2","parentId":"a20a29d6","timestamp":"2026-02-17T18:29:30.019Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning the Approach**\n\nI'm laying out the groundwork for this DMarket project. Currently, I'm focusing on the HTTP/2 and security reporting aspects, ensuring I understand the user's requirements.  The \"Quadriga\" launch simulation is also on my mind, but I'm prioritizing the security considerations. I will be ready to begin providing specific answers soon.\n\n\n**Analyzing the Requirements**\n\nI've refined my understanding of the tasks. The key deliverable is secure documentation, followed by refactoring the `src/core/network.py` file. The file refactoring requires an HFTClient implementation, built on `httpx`, HTTP/2, connection management, and the client startup offset. I am thinking of a modular approach to handle the client's startup offset, and the connection pools.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771352969886_19","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"dir /s /b src"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771352970014_20","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"type src\\core\\network.py"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4885,"output":166,"cacheRead":4513,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5051,"cost":{"input":0.00977,"output":0.001992,"cacheRead":0.0009026,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012664599999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771352956984}}
